{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"3343","heading":"Security clearances; limitations","label":"3343 Security clearances; limitations","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/ch45/schIII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextExecutive Order 12958, referred to in subsec. (a)(4), which was formerly set out as a note under section 435 (now section 3161) of this title, was revoked by Ex. Ord. No. 13526, § 6.2(g), , 75 F.R. 731.Dec. 29, 2009","CodificationSection was formerly classified to prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.section 435c of this title","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Change of NameCommittee on Oversight and Government Reform of House of Representatives changed to Committee on Oversight and Reform of House of Representatives by House Resolution No. 6, One Hundred Sixteenth Congress, . Committee on Oversight and Reform of House of Representatives changed to Committee on Oversight and Accountability of House of Representatives by House Resolution No. 5, One Hundred Eighteenth Congress, .Jan. 9, 2019Jan. 9, 2023"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Definitions","label":"a Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Controlled substance","label":"1 Controlled substance","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “controlled substance” has the meaning given that term in .section 802 of title 21","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Covered person","label":"2 Covered person","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/a/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fa%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an officer or employee of a Federal agency;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/a/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fa%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a member of the Army, Navy, Air Force, or Marine Corps who is on active duty or is in an active status; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/a/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fa%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an officer or employee of a contractor of a Federal agency.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Restricted Data","label":"3 Restricted Data","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Restricted Data” has the meaning given that term in .section 2014 of title 42","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":"Special access program","label":"4 Special access program","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “special access program” has the meaning given that term in section 4.1 of Executive Order No. 12958 (60 Fed. Reg. 19825).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Prohibition","label":"b Prohibition","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"After , the head of a Federal agency may not grant or renew a security clearance for a covered person who is an unlawful user of a controlled substance or an addict (as defined in ).January 1, 2008section 802(1) of title 21","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Disqualification","label":"c Disqualification","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"has been convicted in any court of the United States of a crime, was sentenced to imprisonment for a term exceeding 1 year, and was incarcerated as a result of that sentence for not less than 1 year;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"has been discharged or dismissed from the Armed Forces under dishonorable conditions; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is mentally incompetent, as determined by an adjudicating authority, based on an evaluation by a duly qualified mental health professional employed by, or acceptable to and approved by, the United States Government and in accordance with the adjudicative guidelines required by subsection (d).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Waiver authority","label":"2 Waiver authority","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"standards and procedures prescribed by, or under the authority of, an Executive order or other guidance issued by the President; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the adjudicative guidelines required by subsection (d).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Covered security clearances","label":"3 Covered security clearances","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"special access programs;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Restricted Data; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/3/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F3%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any other information commonly referred to as “sensitive compartmented information”.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":"Annual report","label":"4 Annual report","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"Requirement for report","label":"A Requirement for report","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F4%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not later than February 1 of each year, the head of a Federal agency shall submit a report to the appropriate committees of Congress if such agency employs or employed a person for whom a waiver was granted in accordance with paragraph (2) during the preceding year. Such annual report shall not reveal the identity of such person, but shall include for each waiver issued the disqualifying factor under paragraph (1) and the reasons for the waiver of the disqualifying factor.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Definitions","label":"B Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F4%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":"Appropriate committees of Congress","label":"i Appropriate committees of Congress","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F4%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/B/i/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/B/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F4%2FB%2Fi%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the congressional defense committees;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/B/i/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/B/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F4%2FB%2Fi%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the congressional intelligence committees;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"III","heading":null,"label":"III","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/B/i/III","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/B/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F4%2FB%2Fi%2FIII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Committee on Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs of the Senate;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"IV","heading":null,"label":"IV","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/B/i/IV","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/B/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F4%2FB%2Fi%2FIV","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Committee on Oversight and Government Reform of the House of Representatives; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"V","heading":null,"label":"V","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/B/i/V","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/B/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F4%2FB%2Fi%2FV","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"each Committee of the Senate or the House of Representatives with oversight authority over such Federal agency.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":"Congressional defense committees","label":"ii Congressional defense committees","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F4%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “congressional defense committees” has the meaning given that term in .section 101(a)(16) of title 10","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":"Congressional intelligence committees","label":"iii Congressional intelligence committees","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/B/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/c/4/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fc%2F4%2FB%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “congressional intelligence committees” has the meaning given that term in .section 3003 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Adjudicative guidelines","label":"d Adjudicative guidelines","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Requirement to establish","label":"1 Requirement to establish","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The President shall establish adjudicative guidelines for determining eligibility for access to classified information.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Requirements related to mental health","label":"2 Requirements related to mental health","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/d/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/d/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fd%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"include procedures and standards under which a covered person is determined to be mentally incompetent and provide a means to appeal such a determination; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/d/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t50/s3343/d/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft50%2Fs3343%2Fd%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"require that no negative inference concerning the standards in the guidelines may be raised solely on the basis of seeking mental health counseling.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}
